article.headline: Eastern Kentucky 67, Austin Peay 63 (OT)
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Michael Haney scored 23 points as Eastern Kentucky snapped Austin Peay's 21-game Ohio Valley Conference win streak with a 67-63 overtime victory Thursday night. Eastern Kentucky (10-4, 2-1) scored the last four points of the game and held the Governors (4-11, 2-1) scoreless in the last minute. Austin Peay scored its last basket with 1:01 left in the extra period on a William Durden free throw. Haney hit a layup off an assist by Matt Witt for the first score of overtime with 4:01 left. Jason McLeish scored 11 points for Eastern Kentucky and Witt added 10. Austin Peay's Anthony Davis missed a 3-point shot with 31 seconds left in the second half to send it to overtime tied at 58-all. The Governors used a balanced scoring attack with Zac Schlader and Maurice Hampton scoring 14 points each. Davis and Durden added 12 each. The Governors had last lost a conference game two years ago at Eastern Illinois.
